article.headline: Northwestern 69, Bucknell 61
article.story: EVANSTON, Ill. (AP) -- Jitim Young had 20 points and 12 rebounds as Northwestern defeated Bucknell 69-61 on Wednesday night. T.J. Parker added 14 points and Evan Seacat had nine for Northwestern (3-3), which never trailed in the game. The Wildcats opened the game with a 15-5 run, capped by a basket by Young, who extended the lead with a steal and a layup to put Northwestern up 32-16 with 7:06 left in the first half. Bucknell (0-4) cut Northwestern's lead to 53-47 on Kevin Bettencourt's 3-pointer with 8:54 to go. But Northwestern responded with a 10-0 run that ended with a running hook shot by Davor Duvancic that gave the Widcats a 63-47 lead with 5:13 left. Chris McNaughton scored 22 points for the Bison, while Bettencourt added 11. Bucknell made all nine of its free throw attempts and outrebounded Northwestern 36-25. But the Wildcats outshot the Bisons from the field, connecting on 54 percent, compared to 42 percent for Bucknell.
